# DiaEase — project context

## Root

- **Repository root for this app:** `DiaEase/` (same directory as `package.json`).
- Local env: `.env.local` (already present; never commit secrets).
- Prefer paths relative to this root when editing or importing.

## Layout (authoritative)

```
DiaEase/
  app/
    api/
      analyse/route.ts
      explain/route.ts
      simulate/route.ts
      session/route.ts
      alerts/route.ts
      passport/route.ts
  lib/
    iob-calculator.ts
    circadian.ts
    risk-engine.ts
    simulation-engine.ts
    supabase.ts
  types/
    index.ts
```

- **API:** Next.js App Router route handlers under `app/api/<name>/route.ts`. Keep HTTP concerns (request/response, validation, auth) in routes; delegate domain logic to `lib/`.
- **lib/:** Pure or side-effect–bounded modules (calculations, engines, Supabase client). Reuse from routes and server code; avoid importing server-only modules into client components without `"use client"` boundaries respected.
- **types/:** Shared TypeScript types and interfaces; export from `types/index.ts` for a single import surface.

## Next.js

This stack may differ from older Next.js docs. Before changing App Router APIs, layouts, or data fetching, check the guide under `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` in this project and follow deprecation notices.

## Conventions

- Match existing naming, imports, and error-handling patterns in nearby files.
- Keep changes scoped to the task; no unrelated refactors or extra markdown files unless asked.
